cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NI 

The paper proposes a new computational model for visual perception tasks using neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper focuses on early stage visual perception tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The proposed model is based on adaptive neuron cell models, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also compares the proposed model with state-of-the-art algorithms, indicating that it could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Finally, the paper discusses the differences between the proposed model and biological neurons, which could make it relevant to cs.NI (Neuroscience and Neural Systems).
